article.headline: Wagner 70, Mount St. Mary's, Md. 65
article.story: NEW YORK -- Senior Justin Drummond had a career-high 23 points and Wagner defeated Mount St. Mary's 70-65 on Thursday night. Joey Mundweiler added 12 points for the Seahawks (13-13, 5-10 Northeast), who held a 34-30 lead at the half. Shawn Atupem scored 15 points for the Mountaineers (15-11, 11-5). Jeremy Goode and Jean Cajou had 14 points each. Cajou hit a 3-pointer to tie the score at 63-63 with 2:02 to go. The Seahawks took the lead for good at 65-63 on a jumper by Llew Radford.
